Package io.github.hakkelt.ndarrays

Class RealNDArrayReshapeView<T extends Number>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<T>
      • io.github.hakkelt.ndarrays.AbstractNDArray<T,​T2>
        • io.github.hakkelt.ndarrays.RealNDArrayReshapeView<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NDArray<T>, RealNDArray<T>, Iterable<T>, Collection<T>
    public class RealNDArrayReshapeView<T extends Number>
extends AbstractNDArray<T,​T2>
implements RealNDArray<T>
    A view for an NDArray holding real values that changes the shape of the parent NDArray. When reshape(...) is called for a real NDArray, an instance of this class is returned.

        Description copied from interface: NDArray
        Sets the value of an element specified by cartesian indexing.

        Cartesian indexing: The ordinary way to index into an N-dimensional array is to use exactly N indices; each index selects the position(s) in its particular dimension.

        Negative indexing is supported, e.g. assuming a 3×4 NDArray, index [2,-1] equals to [2,3], and [-1,-3] is an equivalent of [2,1].
